able Garbage Collector","url":"https://fil-c.org/fugc","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"vi_mi","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c","plt"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/q7b1gm","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/q7b1gm/fil_s_unbelievable_garbage_collector"},{"short_id":"dfxhug","created_at":"2025-09-04T22:38:25.000-05:00","title":"Stop Shipping PNGs In Your Games","url":"https://gamesbymason.com/blog/2025/stop-shipping-pngs/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"Aks","user_is_author":false,"tags":["games"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dfxhug","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dfxhug/stop_shipping_pngs_your_games"},{"short_id":"uxbodb","created_at":"2025-09-04T22:30:31.000-05:00","title":"Trying to Make Sense of Casing Conventions on the Web","url":"https://blog.jim-nielsen.com/2025/casing-on-the-web/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"abhin4v","user_is_author":false,"tags":["web"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/uxbodb","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/uxbodb/trying_make_sense_casing_conventions_on"},{"short_id":"qdsiyi","created_at":"2025-09-04T21:40:12.000-05:00","title":"Evolving the OCaml Programming Language (2025)","url":"https://kcsrk.info/slides/Evolution_Ashoka_2025.pdf","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"veqq","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ml","pdf"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qdsiyi","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/qdsiyi/evolving_ocaml_programming_language"},{"short_id":"az6oq3","created_at":"2025-09-04T20:57:21.000-05:00","title":"Wolves in the Repository: A Software Engineering Analysis of the XZ Utils Supply Chain Attack","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.17473","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"df","user_is_author":false,"tags":["pdf","security"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/az6oq3","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/az6oq3/wolves_repository_software_engineering"},{"short_id":"kzxxky","created_at":"2025-09-04T17:01:44.000-05:00","title":"maak: The infinitely extensible command runner and automation project build system à la Make","url":"https://codeberg.org/jjba23/maak","score":3,"flags":0,"comment_count":3,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jjba23","user_is_author":true,"tags":["lisp"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kzxxky","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kzxxky/maak_infinitely_extensible_command"},{"short_id":"yekcmn","created_at":"2025-09-04T16:53:50.000-05:00","title":"Cassandra counter columns: Nice in theory, hazardous in practice (2022)","url":"https://ably.com/blog/cassandra-counter-columns-nice-in-theory-hazardous-in-practice","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"neil_f","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","distributed"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yekcmn","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/yekcmn/cassandra_counter_columns_nice_theory"},{"short_id":"gkzmfy","created_at":"2025-09-04T16:46:00.000-05:00","title":"Let's rename the \"vibecoding\" tag to \"llms\"","url":"","score":71,"flags":1,"comment_count":45,"description":"\u003cp\u003eWhen Lobste.rs introduced the “vibe coding” tag to mean any post relating to LLMs part of \u003ca href=\"https://lobste.rs/s/lkngrz/new_tag_vibecoding\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ethe justification for that decision\u003c/a\u003e was this, where the \u003cstrong\u003eindustry is settling on\u003c/strong\u003e link targeted the O’Reilly “Vibe Coding: The Future of Programming” page (\u003ca href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20250417003503/https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/vibe-coding-the/9798341634749/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eInternet Archive here\u003c/a\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe kicked around a bunch of ideas, but \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vibe_coding\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003evibe coding\u003c/a\u003e seems to be the term the \u003ca href=\"https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/vibe-coding-the/9798341634749/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eindustry is settling on\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThat O’Reilly book has been renamed! It’s now called “Beyond Vibe Coding: From Coder to AI-Era Developer”, acknowledging that Vibe Coding is the act of prompting an LLM to produce software without caring about or reviewing the code.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere’s more from the author’s \u003ca href=\"https://beyond.addy.ie/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003esite about the book\u003c/a\u003e:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVibe coding was never meant to describe all AI-assisted coding. It’s a specific approach where you don’t read the AI’s code before running it. There’s much more to consider beyond the prototype for production systems. […]\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAI-assisted engineering is a more structured approach that combines the creativity of vibe coding with the rigor of traditional engineering practices. It involves specs, rigor and emphasizes collaboration between human developers and AI tools, ensuring that the final product is not only functional but also maintainable and secure.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eNow that the O’Reilly have accepted the \u003ca href=\"https://simonwillison.net/2025/Mar/19/vibe-coding/\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eoriginal Karpathy definition\u003c/a\u003e of “vibe coding”, maybe Lobste.rs could too? I think the obvious better name for the tag at this point, given the way it has been used for the past four months, is simply \u003cstrong\u003ellms\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"When Lobste.rs introduced the \"vibe coding\" tag to mean any post relating to LLMs part of [the justification for that decision](https://lobste.rs/s/lkngrz/new_tag_vibecoding) was this, where the **industry is settling on** link targeted the O'Reilly \"Vibe Coding: The Future of Programming\" page ([Internet Archive here](https://web.archive.org/web/20250417003503/https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/vibe-coding-the/9798341634749/)).\r\n\r\n\u003e We kicked around a bunch of ideas, but [vibe coding](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vibe_coding) seems to be the term the [industry is settling on](https://www.oreilly.com/library/view/vibe-coding-the/9798341634749/).\r\n\r\nThat O'Reilly book has been renamed! It's now called \"Beyond Vibe Coding: From Coder to AI-Era Developer\", acknowledging that Vibe Coding is the act of prompting an LLM to produce software without caring about or reviewing the code.\r\n\r\nHere's more from the author's [site about the book](https://beyond.addy.ie/):\r\n\r\n\u003e Vibe coding was never meant to describe all AI-assisted coding. It's a specific approach where you don't read the AI's code before running it. There's much more to consider beyond the prototype for production systems. [...]\r\n\u003e\r\n\u003e AI-assisted engineering is a more structured approach that combines the creativity of vibe coding with the rigor of traditional engineering practices. It involves specs, rigor and emphasizes collaboration between human developers and AI tools, ensuring that the final product is not only functional but also maintainable and secure.\r\n\r\nNow that the O'Reilly have accepted the [original Karpathy definition](https://simonwillison.net/2025/Mar/19/vibe-coding/) of \"vibe coding\", maybe Lobste.rs could too? I think the obvious better name for the tag at this point, given the way it has been used for the past four months, is simply **llms**.","submitter_user":"simonw","user_is_author":true,"tags":["meta","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gkzmfy","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/gkzmfy/let_s_rename_vibecoding_tag_llms"},{"short_id":"szneus","created_at":"2025-09-04T16:30:37.000-05:00","title":"Fast and Accurate Color Depth Conversion (2015)","url":"https://threadlocalmutex.com/?p=48","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"pekkavaa","user_is_author":false,"tags":["graphics"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/szneus","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/szneus/fast_accurate_color_depth_conversion"},{"short_id":"kqm5ks","created_at":"2025-09-04T15:16:20.000-05:00","title":"Glamorous Toolkit: The Moldable Development Environment","url":"https://github.com/feenkcom/gtoolkit","score":7,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"jasonjmcghee","user_is_author":false,"tags":["editors","programming"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kqm5ks","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/kqm5ks/glamorous_toolkit_moldable_development"},{"short_id":"cruxfx","created_at":"2025-09-04T14:50:45.000-05:00","title":"Classic 8×8-pixel B\u0026W Mac patterns","url":"https://www.pauladamsmith.com/blog/2025/09/classic-mac-patterns.html","score":11,"flags":0,"comment_count":2,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"carlana","user_is_author":false,"tags":["retrocomputing"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cruxfx","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/cruxfx/classic_8x8_pixel_b_w_mac_patterns"},{"short_id":"lzr0ug","created_at":"2025-09-04T14:21:25.000-05:00","title":"wal3: A Write-Ahead Log for Chroma, Build on Object Storage","url":"https://trychroma.com/engineering/wal3","score":4,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"av","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","distributed"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lzr0ug","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/lzr0ug/wal3_write_ahead_log_for_chroma_build_on"},{"short_id":"yvua2g","created_at":"2025-09-04T14:15:30.000-05:00","title":"Subverting code integrity checks to locally backdoor Signal, 1Password, Slack, and more","url":"https://blog.trailofbits.com/2025/09/03/s